Fieldcrest Cannon Inc is raising 110mln dlrs through an offering of convertible subordinateddebentures due 2012 with a six pct coupon and par pricing, saidsole underwriter Kidder, Peabody and Co Inc.    The debentures are convertible into the company's commonstock at 44.25 dlrs per share, representing a premium of 26.43pct over the stock price when terms on the debt were set.    Non-callable for two years, the debt is rated Ba-2 byMoody's Investors Service Inc and BB-minus by Standard andPoor's Corp. The issue was increased from an initial offeringof 100 mln dlrs because of investor demand. Reuter&#3;